articles.title: Alphabet (GOOG) stock price rises after hours as Google settles $68 million Assistant privacy case
articles.summary: Alphabet (GOOG) stock rose 1.6% in after-hours trading following news that Google settled a $68 million privacy case related to its Assistant recording "false accepts." Investors are also anticipating the Federal Reserve's policy decision due Wednesday and Alphabet's earnings report on February 4th. The company faces additional legal challenges, including a lawsuit concerning youth mental health impacts of YouTube.

articles.title: Revvity declares quarterly dividend of $0.07 per share
articles.summary: Revvity, Inc. announced a regular quarterly dividend of $0.07 per share, payable on May 8, 2026, to shareholders of record as of April 17, 2026. This dividend marks the company's 56th consecutive year of payments, reflecting a current yield of 0.24%. Despite trading at a premium valuation with a market cap of $13.02 billion and a P/E ratio of 59.38, the health science solutions provider is set to report its next quarterly earnings in three days.

articles.title: Jim Cramer Expects Western Digital’s Quarter to Be “Very Positive”
articles.summary: Jim Cramer predicted a "very positive" quarter for Western Digital Corporation (NASDAQ: WDC), noting that both Western Digital and SanDisk are key storage plays. He highlighted Western Digital's strong performance in Q3 2025, being up almost 88%, and its importance as a pure-play data storage company. Cramer also reminisced about his past belief in the company's value, expressing satisfaction that the market is now recognizing its worth.

articles.title: Intel's Make-or-Break Foundry Moment Arrives This Year
articles.summary: Intel's foundry business faces a critical year as it seeks external customers for its advanced manufacturing processes, particularly Intel 14A. While the Intel 18A process is producing chips internally, major external customer commitments are lacking. CEO Lip-Bu Tan emphasizes that future capacity for Intel 14A relies on securing these customer deals, making 2026 a make-or-break year for the company's long-term foundry strategy.

articles.title: IWO vs. VONG: How Does A Small Cap Growth Compare Against A Large Cap Growth Fund
articles.summary: This article compares two growth ETFs, VONG and IWO, highlighting their differences in focus, cost, performance, and holdings. VONG tracks large-cap growth stocks, primarily in tech, while IWO focuses on small-cap growth stocks across various sectors. Investors should consider their risk tolerance and investment goals when choosing between VONG's large-cap tech concentration and IWO's small-cap diversification.

articles.title: Market Movers: iShares Silver Trust Up 12%
articles.summary: The iShares Silver Trust (SLV) has seen a significant 12% increase, with silver prices reaching historic highs above $115, attributed to structural deficits, industrial demand, and safe-haven buying. Additionally, USA Rare Earth (USAR) surged 18% after receiving a $1.3 billion loan and $277 million in federal funding from the Trump Administration. JPMorgan also raised Apple's (AAPL) price target to $315, citing strong iPhone demand ahead of its first-quarter earnings report.

articles.title: Should iShares Russell 1000 Growth ETF (IWF) Be on Your Investing Radar?
articles.summary: The iShares Russell 1000 Growth ETF (IWF) offers broad exposure to the Large Cap Growth segment of the US equity market. Launched in 2000, it has over $121.09 billion in assets and a low expense ratio of 0.18%. The ETF is concentrated in the Information Technology sector, with top holdings including Nvidia, Apple, and Microsoft, and has received a Zacks ETF Rank of 1 (Strong Buy).

articles.title: Logitech Upgrades Hybrid Meeting Experience With Rally AI Cameras
articles.summary: Logitech has introduced two new AI-powered conference cameras, Rally AI Camera and Rally AI Camera Pro, designed to enhance video meetings in large spaces with features like dual-camera setup, 1-inch imaging sensors, and advanced AI framing. These cameras, along with recent product launches like the Muse digital pencil for Apple Vision Pro and solar-powered keyboards, demonstrate Logitech's focus on innovative solutions for hybrid work and creativity. The company aims to meet the growing demand for improved remote work setups and productivity tools by collaborating with major tech platforms.

articles.title: Logitech Upgrades Hybrid Meeting Experience With Rally AI Cameras
articles.summary: Logitech has unveiled two new AI-powered conference cameras, the Rally AI Camera and Rally AI Camera Pro, designed to enhance hybrid meeting experiences in large spaces. These cameras feature dual setups, AI framing with RightSight 2, and facilitate easier setup and room usage tracking for IT teams. These new introductions, alongside recent products like the Muse digital pencil for Apple Vision Pro and solar-powered keyboards, highlight Logitech's commitment to innovation in supporting evolving work and creativity needs.

articles.title: Qualcomm, Skyworks PT trimmed as handset outlook weakens By Investing.com
articles.summary: Mizuho lowered price targets for Qualcomm (NASDAQ:QCOM) and Skyworks (NASDAQ:SWKS) due to a weakening handset outlook. The firm expects global handset shipments to fall by about 4% in 2026, with Chinese original design manufacturers expected to cut output by 10%. Memory price increases and supply shortages are key factors impacting production, particularly affecting Android makers, while Apple (NASDAQ:AAPL) is gaining market share in China.

articles.title: Apple unveils long-awaited updated AirTag (AAPL:NASDAQ)
articles.summary: Apple has announced a new version of its AirTag item finder, featuring an extended range compared to its predecessor. The updated device is now available for order on Apple's website, with in-store availability expected "soon." The article also notes the initial publication time as January 26, 2026, at 9:16 AM ET.

articles.title: TikTok’s Khaby Lame Secures Landmark $900M Deal with Rich Sparkle Holdings, Redefining Creator Economy Scale
articles.summary: TikTok star Khaby Lame has finalized a groundbreaking $900 million to $975 million all-stock deal with U.S.-listed Rich Sparkle Holdings. This transaction involves the partial sale of Lame's operating company and grants Rich Sparkle exclusive global commercial rights to his brand for 36 months, aiming to transform his viral persona into a platform-integrated business empire. The deal also includes the development of an AI-powered digital twin of Lame and targets over $4 billion in annual sales.

articles.title: Is Schwab Fundamental U.S. Large Company ETF (FNDX) a Strong ETF Right Now?
articles.summary: The Schwab Fundamental U.S. Large Company ETF (FNDX), launched in 2013, is a smart beta ETF focused on large-cap value stocks, managing over $23.14 billion in assets. It tracks the Russell RAFI US Large Co. Index, aiming to outperform market-cap weighted indexes through a fundamental weighting strategy. FNDX has an expense ratio of 0.25%, a dividend yield of 1.58%, and has shown a 15.93% return over the past year, making it a medium-risk option for investors.

articles.title: Is FlexShares Morningstar U.S. Market Factor Tilt ETF (TILT) a Strong ETF Right Now?
articles.summary: The article analyzes the FlexShares Morningstar U.S. Market Factor Tilt ETF (TILT), a smart beta ETF that debuted in 2011. It highlights TILT's objective to outperform the Style Box - All Cap Blend segment by tilting towards small-capitalization and value stocks, detailing its expense ratio, sector exposure, top holdings, and performance. The article also compares TILT to alternative ETFs like ITOT and VTI, suggesting that traditional market cap-weighted ETFs might be cheaper and lower-risk options for some investors.

articles.title: SCHD: Horrible Year Reinforces Flaws (NYSEARCA:SCHD)
articles.summary: This article argues that the Schwab U.S. Dividend Equity ETF (SCHD) is structurally designed to underperform the S&P 500. The author contends that SCHD's restrictive selection criteria, such as the 10-year dividend history requirement, exclude high-growth stocks, leading to missed upside. Additionally, annual reconstitution and the removal of certain sectors are cited as reasons for its underperformance, reinforcing a bearish thesis on SCHD.

articles.title: Is FlexShares Morningstar U.S. Market Factor Tilt ETF (TILT) a Strong ETF Right Now?
articles.summary: The article analyzes the FlexShares Morningstar U.S. Market Factor Tilt ETF (TILT), a smart beta ETF launched in 2011 with over $1.89 billion in assets. It highlights TILT's objective to outperform the Style Box - All Cap Blend segment by tilting towards small-capitalization and value stocks, noting its 0.25% expense ratio and recent performance. The piece also compares it to traditional market-cap weighted ETFs like ITOT and VTI as alternatives.

articles.title: Alphabet Inc. $GOOGL Stock Holdings Lifted by Smith Shellnut Wilson LLC ADV
articles.summary: Smith Shellnut Wilson LLC ADV significantly increased its stake in Alphabet Inc. (GOOGL) by 95.7% in Q3, now owning 5,246 shares valued at $1.275 million. This coincides with positive sentiment for Alphabet, driven by partnerships like Apple tying Gemini to Siri and several analyst price target upgrades. However, the company faces regulatory and safety concerns, including a probe into Waymo robotaxis and an antitrust lawsuit regarding Google's default-search payments.

articles.title: Portfolio Anchors: SCHB Offers Broader Growth Exposure While VTV Delivers Value and a Higher Yield
articles.summary: This article compares two ETFs, SCHB and VTV, highlighting their distinct investment strategies. SCHB offers broad US equity market exposure with a significant tech tilt and higher growth potential, while VTV focuses on large-cap value stocks, providing a higher dividend yield and lower volatility. Investors can choose between SCHB for capital appreciation or VTV for lower risk returns and income.

articles.title: Markets Brief: What to Watch in Big Tech Earnings, Plus the Fed Meeting
articles.summary: This week brings a busy schedule of corporate and macroeconomic news, with major tech companies like Tesla, Microsoft, Meta, and Apple reporting earnings. Investors will also be watching the Federal Reserve meeting, where officials are expected to keep interest rates on hold, with Fed Chair Jerome Powell likely to emphasize data-dependent decisions. Analysts provide insights into key areas to watch for each company, including Tesla's robotaxi plans, Microsoft's AI developments, Meta's capital spending concerns, and Apple's iPhone sales.

articles.title: Earnings To Watch: General Motors (GM) Reports Q4 Results Tomorrow
articles.summary: General Motors (NYSE:GM) is set to report its Q4 earnings tomorrow before market open. Analysts anticipate a 4% year-on-year revenue decline to $45.81 billion and adjusted earnings of $2.26 per share, despite the company's consistent track record of exceeding revenue estimates in the past. Investors are keenly watching GM as sentiment in the broader industrials segment has shown positive growth.

articles.title: Qorvo stock drifts into earnings week: what to watch for QRVO before Tuesday’s report
articles.summary: Qorvo Inc. shares slipped ahead of its fiscal third-quarter earnings report, scheduled for Tuesday after market close. Investors will be closely watching for signs of demand for RF chips, profit margins, and any updates regarding its proposed merger with Skyworks Solutions. The report's implications will be further understood in the context of Apple's earnings report later in the week, significantly influencing sentiment towards parts suppliers.

articles.title: ASE Technology stock (ASX) near a 52-week high as Fed and Big Tech earnings loom
articles.summary: ASE Technology (ASX) shares closed near a 52-week high, gaining 1.7%, as investors anticipate the Federal Reserve's decision and upcoming mega-cap tech earnings, particularly those linked to AI. The company, a key player in chip packaging and testing, is scheduled to release its fourth-quarter earnings on February 5th. Investors will focus on these earnings and broader tech guidance to gauge AI investment impact and future demand, especially given the stock's proximity to its yearly high.

articles.title: Portfolio Anchors: SCHB Offers Broader Growth Exposure While VTV Delivers Value and a Higher Yield
articles.summary: This article compares two popular ETFs, SCHB and VTV, highlighting their differing approaches for investors. SCHB offers broad US equity market exposure with a tech bias, aiming for higher capital appreciation, while VTV focuses on large-cap value stocks, providing a higher dividend yield and lower volatility. The comparison covers their costs, performance, and sector exposures to help investors choose based on their priorities.

articles.title: Portfolio Anchors: SCHB Offers Broader Growth Exposure While VTV Delivers Value and a Higher Yield
articles.summary: This article compares two ETFs, SCHB and VTV, highlighting their distinct investment approaches. SCHB provides broad U.S. equity market exposure with a tech-heavy tilt, offering higher growth potential, while VTV focuses on large-cap value stocks, providing a higher dividend yield and lower volatility. The choice between them depends on an investor's preference for growth versus value and risk tolerance.

articles.title: Is Globalstar’s (GSAT) Antenna Build-Out Quietly Redefining Its Long-Term Network Advantage?
articles.summary: Globalstar (GSAT) has expanded its C-3 Satellite System with new antennas in South Korea, part of a global build-out to enhance its network for next-generation services and IoT. This expansion strengthens Globalstar's long-term network capability, underpinning its strategy to serve remote and critical connectivity markets. While the antenna build-out reinforces existing offerings, near-term catalysts for GSAT's investment narrative still depend on monetizing wholesale capacity, expanding government and defense demand, and achieving consistent profitability.

articles.title: A Shift in Leadership: NVIDIA Tops Holdings in iShares MSCI World ETF
articles.summary: The iShares MSCI World ETF (URTH) has seen a significant shift in its top holdings, with NVIDIA surpassing Apple and Microsoft to become its largest single position, now over 5% of the portfolio. This indicates a growing concentration in major U.S. technology stocks, despite URTH's robust performance in 2025. The article highlights the fund's portfolio concentration, compares it to other global ETFs, and discusses its forward outlook, including an anticipated index rebalance in February 2026.

articles.title: 1 S&P 500 ETF to Invest in if The Market Crashes in 2026
articles.summary: This article suggests the Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight ETF (RSP) as a safer investment alternative for those concerned about a potential market crash in 2026. Unlike the standard S&P 500, which is heavily concentrated in "Magnificent Seven" tech stocks, RSP gives equal weight to all companies, offering better diversification across sectors less vulnerable during downturns, like consumer staples and utilities. While the standard S&P 500 has outperformed in recent years due to its tech focus, RSP aims to reduce risk by mitigating the impact of any tech-specific corrections.

articles.title: 1 S&P 500 ETF to Invest in if The Market Crashes in 2026
articles.summary: This article suggests investing in the Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight ETF (RSP) as a way to reduce risk in a potentially volatile market, especially if a market crash occurs in 2026. Unlike the standard S&P 500, which is heavily concentrated in a few large tech stocks, RSP weights all companies equally, providing broader diversification across sectors that tend to perform better during downturns. The article highlights that while the standard S&P 500 has outperformed in recent years due to tech concentration, RSP offers a safer alternative for investors concerned about the market's current high valuations.

articles.title: Alphabet Inc. $GOOGL is PKO Investment Management Joint Stock Co's 6th Largest Position
articles.summary: PKO Investment Management Joint Stock Co reduced its stake in Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ:GOOGL) by 13.8% in Q3, making it their 6th largest holding worth $33.55 million. Despite insider selling valued at $68.56 million, institutional investors hold 40.03% of the stock. Analysts show broad positive sentiment with a consensus "Moderate Buy" rating and a target price of $331.40, driven by AI monetization and partnerships, while facing regulatory risks from Waymo probes and antitrust lawsuits.

articles.title: Torray Investment Partners LLC Sells 2,171 Shares of Apple Inc. $AAPL
articles.summary: Torray Investment Partners LLC has reduced its stake in Apple Inc. (NASDAQ:AAPL) by 3.9%, selling 2,171 shares to hold a total of 53,411 shares valued at $13.6 million. This makes Apple its 24th largest holding, representing about 1.8% of Torray's portfolio. Despite this reduction by one fund, other large institutional investors like Vanguard, State Street, and Norges Bank have significant or increasing positions in Apple, collectively owning 67.73% of the company.

articles.title: Memory chip makers lead market gains amid AI-driven supply crunch
articles.summary: Memory chip manufacturers like Micron Technology, Western Digital, and Seagate are experiencing significant market gains due to an AI-driven supply crunch. Micron's stock rose over 250% in the past year, with robust earnings growth projected. The high demand for HBM chips for AI data centers is driving up prices for DRAM and NAND, benefiting producers but increasing costs for customers like Apple and HP, and potentially leading to a market contraction in smartphone and PC sectors into 2027.

articles.title: A Deep Dive into the iShares MSCI ACWI ETF: A Global Investment Vehicle Examined
articles.summary: This article provides a detailed analysis of the iShares MSCI ACWI ETF (US4642882579), highlighting its composition, performance, and key competitive factors. It notes the ETF's significant concentration in U.S. equities and technology giants like Nvidia, Apple, and Microsoft, and discusses its solid performance in early 2026 despite higher expense ratios compared to competitors. The analysis also touches on the future outlook, considering the impact of AI momentum and current valuation concerns in the market.

articles.title: Why Wall Street Is Wrong About Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Stock
articles.summary: This article argues that Wall Street's consensus price target for Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing (TSMC) is too low, despite 98% of analysts rating it a buy. The author believes TSMC's stock can go "much higher" due to increasing demand for semiconductors from the AI industry, the company's dominant market position, and its attractive P/E ratio. TSMC's plans to increase capital expenditure and projected 30% sales growth in 2026 are highlighted as key drivers for future stock performance.

articles.title: What To Expect From Agilysys's (AGYS) Q4 Earnings
articles.summary: Agilysys (AGYS) is set to announce its Q4 earnings on Monday after market close. Analysts anticipate a 14% year-on-year revenue growth to $79.28 million and adjusted earnings of $0.46 per share. Despite Agilysys's stock being down 11.4% over the last month, the average analyst price target is $142, significantly higher than its current share price of $107.70.

articles.title: A Closer Look at the Amplify CWP Enhanced Dividend Income ETF's Active Approach ()
articles.summary: The Amplify CWP Enhanced Dividend Income ETF (DIVO) utilizes an active strategy of buying high-quality dividend-paying stocks and selling covered calls to generate a high distribution yield. As of early 2026, DIVO boasts a trailing twelve-month yield of approximately 6.3% and a 15.8% total return over the past year, outperforming passive dividend indices. Despite a higher expense ratio of 0.56%, its concentrated portfolio of blue-chip companies and monthly distributions make it attractive to income-seeking investors, with its future performance linked to declining interest rates and robust earnings growth from its holdings.

articles.title: A Closer Look at the Amplify CWP Enhanced Dividend Income ETF's Active Approach ()
articles.summary: The Amplify CWP Enhanced Dividend Income ETF (DIVO) utilizes an active strategy of investing in high-quality dividend stocks and selling covered calls to generate a higher yield than passive dividend ETFs and Treasury notes. Despite a higher expense ratio, DIVO aims for superior income and total returns through its concentrated, quality-driven portfolio and monthly distributions. Its future performance in early 2026 will depend on interest rate movements, the earnings growth of its holdings, and moderate market volatility.

articles.title: Is QUALCOMM (QCOM) One of the Best 5G Stocks to Invest In?
articles.summary: The article discusses QUALCOMM (QCOM) as a potential 5G investment, noting recent analyst ratings and price targets. Citi reiterated a Neutral rating with a $180 price target, while RBC Capital initiated coverage with a Sector Perform rating and a $180 target, citing concerns about smartphone market growth and Apple's modem in-sourcing. Despite these concerns, RBC Capital views QUALCOMM's valuation as reasonable and highlights its solid cash returns and new AI accelerator product.

articles.title: META - Meta Platforms Inc Stock Price and Quote
articles.summary: This article provides comprehensive financial data, news, and insider transaction details for Meta Platforms Inc. (META). It highlights the company's stock performance, key financial metrics, recent news events impacting its share price, and a detailed list of insider stock sales.

articles.title: Evergreen Private Wealth LLC Buys 8,213 Shares of Alphabet Inc. $GOOGL
articles.summary: Evergreen Private Wealth LLC significantly increased its stake in Alphabet (NASDAQ:GOOGL) by 22.2%, purchasing an additional 8,213 shares to reach a total of 45,256 shares valued at $11 million, making it their largest portfolio position. Despite this institutional buying, company insiders, including CEO Sundar Pichai, have been net sellers, offloading shares worth approximately $68.6 million. Market sentiment remains largely positive due to strategic advancements like Apple integrating Gemini with Siri and Google's AI shopping initiatives, though regulatory and Waymo safety concerns present potential headwinds.

articles.title: Amaze Announces Expanded Partnership with Contend to Scale the Next Generation of Creator-Led Commerce
articles.summary: Amaze Holdings, Inc. announced an expanded strategic partnership with Contend, a creative studio that has advised Amaze for some time. This collaboration will integrate Contend's expertise in building audience-first formats that drive demand with Amaze's global commerce platform. The partnership aims to scale creator-led commerce by developing high-conversion product launches across various sectors, enabling creators to build sustainable businesses through immersive storytelling and integrated fulfillment.

articles.title: Intel Continues to Right the Ship in Products and Manufacturing
articles.summary: Intel is working to overcome competitive disadvantages in CPU development and manufacturing against rivals like AMD, Nvidia, and Apple. The company's strategy focuses on stabilizing its PC and server CPU segments while seeking external investment to strengthen Intel Foundry. This effort is aimed at "righting the ship" and closing the gap with its competitors.

articles.title: T-Mobile Activates Free Cellular Starlink in the US As Winter Storm Rolls In
articles.summary: T-Mobile has activated free Starlink cellular service for its customers in areas expected to be affected by Winter Storm Fern, allowing basic text messaging connectivity via satellite when traditional cellular service is disrupted. While T-Satellite typically costs an additional $10 per month, T-Mobile is waiving the fee for compatible phones during the storm. This service also broadcasts Wireless Emergency Alerts and is a proactive measure by carriers to maintain communication during severe weather.

articles.title: First Citizens BancShares (NASDAQ:FCNCA) Surprises With Strong Q4 CY2025
articles.summary: First Citizens BancShares (NASDAQ:FCNCA) exceeded Q4 CY2025 revenue and non-GAAP profit expectations, with sales increasing 9.5% year-on-year to $2.44 billion and adjusted EPS reaching $51.27. The regional banking company demonstrated strong performance in net interest income and tangible book value per share, though its recent revenue growth has decelerated compared to its five-year trend. The results suggest a solid quarter for the bank, prompting further analysis into its long-term fundamentals.

articles.title: From Google X to Panasonic: Yoky Matsuoka joins Analog Devices board
articles.summary: Analog Devices (ADI) has appointed Dr. Yoky Matsuoka, an executive officer at Panasonic Holdings with previous senior roles at Google and Apple, to its Board of Directors as an independent director, effective January 20, 2026. Her appointment expands the board to 11 members and is seen as a strategic move to leverage her expertise in integrating hardware, software, and AI for human-centric systems. Dr. Matsuoka, a MacArthur Genius Award recipient, brings a wealth of experience in technology, robotics, and neuroscience to ADI.

articles.title: Healthcare Triangle Top Nasdaq Stock by Volume - Market Recap Jan 23, 2026 - News and Statistics
articles.summary: On January 23, 2026, Healthcare Triangle Inc. led Nasdaq volume with over 194 million shares traded, closing up $0.0556 at $0.4556. Other top movers included 60 Degrees Pharmaceuticals Inc., MINGTENG INTL CORP INC., and American Rebel Holdings Inc. Major tech stocks like NVIDIA, Intel, AMD, Apple, Microsoft, Tesla, Meta Platforms, Amazon, and Alphabet also saw significant trading activity, primarily closing with gains.

articles.title: Apple’s High-Stakes Earnings: iPhone 17 Cycle and the AI Pivot Face a Market Litmus Test
articles.summary: Apple Inc. is facing a critical fiscal first-quarter earnings report for 2026, where investors will scrutinize the impact of the iPhone 17 product cycle and the adoption of "Apple Intelligence." The company's premium valuation and consumer-first AI strategy are under pressure, with insights expected on its recovery in China, the performance of 12GB RAM Pro models, and the growth of AI-linked Services revenue. This report is seen as a turning point to validate or debunk the "AI Supercycle" and redefine Apple's identity beyond just a hardware company.

articles.title: Wow, iShares OEF ETF Holds 11% in One Single Stock
articles.summary: The iShares S&P 100 ETF (OEF) is heavily concentrated in mega-cap technology stocks, with NVIDIA, Apple, and Microsoft making up 28% of its assets and NVIDIA alone accounting for nearly 11%. While this concentration has driven substantial gains over the past five years, it also creates significant vulnerability during market downturns, as demonstrated by OEF's recent underperformance compared to the broader S&P 500 ETF. OEF is best suited for investors seeking amplified exposure to large-cap U.S. equities with a growth tilt, who are comfortable with the inherent concentration risk.

articles.title: Ahead of Earnings, Is SAP Stock a Buy, a Sell, or Fairly Valued?
articles.summary: Morningstar analyst Rob Hales, CFA, assesses SAP ahead of its Q4 2025 earnings report. Key focuses for investors will be cloud revenue growth, current cloud backlog trends, and the software company's long-term trajectory beyond 2027. SAP currently holds a 4-star "Buy" rating from Morningstar with a Fair Value Estimate of EUR 265.00.

articles.title: Ahead of Earnings, Is Apple Stock a Buy, a Sell, or Fairly Valued?
articles.summary: Morningstar anticipates Apple to release its fiscal Q1 2026 earnings report on January 29, expecting record sales led by the iPhone due to strong holiday demand. The company maintains a 3-star Morningstar Rating, a Wide Economic Moat, and a Medium Uncertainty Rating, with a fair value estimate of $240 per share, suggesting the stock is currently fairly valued. Key points of interest include continued double-digit services revenue growth, commentary on its AI deal with Google Gemini, and the impact of geopolitical and AI-related uncertainties on its stock performance.

articles.title: Amaze Announces Expanded Partnership with Contend to Scale the Next Generation of Creator-Led Commerce
articles.summary: Amaze Holdings, Inc. and Contend have announced an expanded strategic partnership to scale creator-led commerce through immersive storytelling and integrated fulfillment. This collaboration formalizes Contend's role as a strategy advisor, focusing on brand campaigns and go-to-market strategies for Amaze. The partnership aims to enable creators and brands to launch products that seamlessly connect content, community, and conversation, with plans to roll out creator- and brand-led commerce launches throughout 2026.
